President Trump and President Putin held a joint press conference after their meeting in Helsinki. They discussed various topics, including the Russia-United States relationship, global security, nuclear proliferation, counterterrorism, regional crises, and economic cooperation. President Trump mentioned the issue of Russian interference in the 2016 US elections, stating that he trusts both the US intelligence agencies and President Putin. President Putin denied any Russian interference and offered to cooperate with the US in investigating the matter. They also discussed Syria and the possibility of working together to provide humanitarian aid and create safe zones. Overall, both leaders expressed a desire for improved relations and increased cooperation between their countries.